FBIS4-54669 "dreeu086_k_94005" FBIS-EEU-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 CROATIA New Currency To Be Introduced 30 May New Currency To Be Introduced 30 May LD0305180494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 3 May 94 LD0305180494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpts] The Croatian dinar's days are numbered. Croatia will be introducing its own currency on Statehood Day, 30 May. As you already know, this will be the kuna. The dinar will remain legal tender until 7 June, but converting it into the new currency will be possible until the end of the year. This was revealed to reporters this afternoon by National Bank Governor Pero Jurkovic. [passage omitted] The replacement of the Croatian dinar by the new currency of the Republic of Croatia will be realized by knocking off three zeros, according to National Bank Deputy Governor Zdravko Rogic. [passage omitted]
